source.guidance:
The first line needs to be the array declaration. You cannot iterate over an array that does not exist. 

There are three possible choices for the loop. Arrays start at index 0 and go until array.length - 1. That means the correct loop declaration has `int i = 0; i < animals.length;` in it.

Don't forget to indent the print statement and close the loop curly brace.

```java
String[] animals = {"cat", "dog", "fish", "rabbit"};
for(int i = 0; i < animals.length; i++) {
    System.out.println("Animal #" + i + " is a " + animals[i]);
}
```

